Wave: Blue Stardust

When our good friend @noslemonstein told us that he was going to order a custom @trexglass bowl piece, we were sooooo excited and couldn’t wait to see what they could come up with together. This bowl is an absolute 1 of 1 and you won’t be finding anything like this in your local head shop. We love the colours the two decided to go with and they all just work so well together! I personally suggested doing the wave horn because @noslemonstein was a successful swimmer and we just thought it would be perfect for him. I loooooove this bowl and I am so excited to use it!!!

I usually play to my strengths. I’m trying to push myself to play to my weaknesses. I read a book by @davidgoggins That instructs you to do shit you hate every day to be a better person. Some things I hate, working in 110 degrees, pattern work because I have the attention span of a golden retriever, working opposite density colors together and not worrying if my glass sells or not. Lately I’ve been really trying to push myself not just on the torch but in the rest of my life with fitness and relationships and trying to just be more. I slapped this piece together really with no plan and I’m happy with the way it came out. Gonna tweak the shaman design a little bit in the coming months. Stay tuned.
